author: jdcasey
msg: [MNG-3394] Reenabling the project.injectPluginManagementInfo(..) call in DefaultLifecycleExecutor.getMojoDescriptor(..), but also moving the project-plugin search out of the 2-token condition where the prefix is resolved, to below all of the token-parsing but just above the injectPluginManagementInfo call, to allow the project-plugin's version to override if it exists. This fixes the case where the lifecycle specifies a plugin but the project's build/plugins doesn't have the version in it...but the project's build/pluginManagement does.

author: jdcasey
msg: [MNG-3394] Allow plugin versions in the POM's build/plugins section to override versions in the build/pluginManagement section. Also, adding a couple of unit tests trying to narrow down the sources for MNG-3394 and MNG-3355..which turns out to be in the project builder.
